care. Despite restricting mepolizumab use to patients with a higher baseline 
exacerbation rate (3 in the past year) in a scenario analysis, the ICER remained 
high at SGD238 876 (USD 169 602) per QALY gained.
CONCLUSION: At its current price, mepolizumab is not considered a cost-effective 
use of healthcare resources in Singapore. Substantial price reductions for 
mepolizumab are required to improve its cost-effectiveness to an acceptable 
range. These results will be useful to inform national funding decisions.

